12 Chapter 9. Employment of Unauthorized Aliens
13 Sec. 1. As used in this chapter, "agency" means any state or
14 local administration, agency, authority, board, bureau,
15 commission, committee, council, department, division, institution,
16 office, service, or other similar body of government created or
17 established by law that issues any form of operating authorization
18 that is used to engage in commerce in Indiana or in a county, city,
19 town, or township located in Indiana.
20 Sec. 2. As used in this chapter, "employ" means to engage the
21 services or labor of an individual for wages or other remuneration,
22 including to suffer or permit to work.
23 Sec. 3. As used in this chapter, "employee" means an individual
24 who is employed by an employer, including an individual who is
25 suffered or permitted to work.
26 Sec. 4. As used in this chapter, "employer" means a person,
27 including an agent, that employs employees in Indiana.
28 Sec. 5. As used in this chapter, "operating authorization" means
29 a license, permit, certificate, approval, registration, charter, article
30 of incorporation, or other form of authorization that is:
31 (1) issued by an agency; and
32 (2) used by a person to engage in commerce in Indiana or in
33 a county, city, town, or township located in Indiana.
34 Sec. 6. As used in this chapter, "unauthorized alien" has the
35 meaning set forth in 8 U.S.C. 1324a(h)(3).
36 Sec. 7. (a) This subsection does not apply to the hiring,
37 recruitment, or employment of an unauthorized alien that
38 occurred before July 1, 2026. Except as provided in subsection (c),
39 it is unlawful for an employer to knowingly or intentionally recruit,
40 hire, or employ an unauthorized alien in Indiana.
41 (b) For purposes of this chapter, "reasonable diligence to
42 confirm the work eligibility of an individual" includes:
